#. Translators: Title of the macro safety checks dialog.
#. {number} is the macro slot number and {stack} the stack it belongs to.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Safety checks for macro {number} in stack {stack}"
msgstr "Vérifications de sécurité pour la macro {number} de la pile {stack}"

#. Translators: Label of the list showing every recorded step of a macro.
msgid "&Steps:"
msgstr "É&tapes :"

#. Translators: Header of the steps list column holding the recorded keystroke.
msgid "Keystroke"
msgstr "Frappe"

#. Translators: Header of the steps list column holding what NVDA spoke while recording.
msgid "Recorded speech"
msgstr "Parole enregistrée"

#. Translators: Header of the steps list column holding the expected speech pattern.
msgid "Expected speech pattern"
msgstr "Modèle de parole attendu"

#. Translators: Header of the steps list column telling whether the safety check
#. is enforced for that step.
msgid "Enforced"
msgstr "Imposée"

#. Translators: Header of the steps list column holding the delay in seconds
#. waited before pressing that step's key.
msgid "Delay (seconds)"
msgstr "Délai (secondes)"

#. Translators: Label of the edit field holding the expected speech pattern
#. for the selected macro step. * matches any text.
msgid "Expected speech &pattern, use * as a wildcard:"
msgstr "&Modèle de parole attendu, utilisez * comme joker :"

#. Translators: Label of the checkbox that turns safety check enforcement
#. on for the selected macro step.
msgid "&Enforce safety check for this step"
msgstr "&Imposer la vérification de sécurité pour cette étape"

#. Translators: Label of the button that copies the recorded speech of the
#. selected step into its expected speech pattern.
msgid "&Use recorded speech as pattern"
msgstr "&Utiliser la parole enregistrée comme modèle"

#. Translators: Label of the edit field holding the delay in seconds waited
#. before pressing the selected macro step's key.
msgid "&Delay in seconds before pressing this key:"
msgstr "&Délai en secondes avant d'appuyer sur cette touche :"

#. Translators: Shown in the enforced column for steps whose safety check is on.
msgid "Yes"
msgstr "Oui"

#. Translators: Shown in the enforced column for steps whose safety check is off.
msgid "No"
msgstr "Non"

#. Translators: Script category shown in NVDA's input gestures dialog.
#. Add-on summary/title, usually the user visible name of the add-on
msgid "Macros"
msgstr "Macros"

#. Translators: Announced when the macros command layer becomes active.
msgid "Macros layer"
msgstr "Couche de macros"

#. Translators: Input help description for the main macros command.
msgid ""
"Turns the macros layer on or off. While recording a macro, stops recording. "
"While a macro is playing, stops playback."
msgstr ""
"Active ou désactive la couche de macros. Pendant l'enregistrement d'une "
"macro, arrête l'enregistrement. Pendant la lecture d'une macro, arrête la "
"lecture."

#. Translators: Announced when macro playback is interrupted by the user.
msgid "Macro playback stopped"
msgstr "Lecture de la macro arrêtée"

#. Translators: Announced when leaving the macros layer without running a command.
msgid "Macros layer off"
msgstr "Couche de macros désactivée"

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that plays a macro.
msgid "Plays the macro stored in the pressed number slot"
msgstr "Lit la macro enregistrée dans l'emplacement du chiffre pressé"

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that records a macro.
msgid "Starts recording a macro into the pressed number slot"
msgstr "Commence l'enregistrement d'une macro dans l'emplacement du chiffre pressé"

#. Translators: Announced when recording into a slot that already
#. holds a macro. {number} is the macro slot number and {key} the
#. number row key to press again with shift to confirm.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Macro {number} is already recorded, press shift+{key} again to overwrite it"
msgstr ""
"La macro {number} est déjà enregistrée, appuyez à nouveau sur maj+{key} "
"pour la remplacer"

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that edits macro safety checks.
msgid "Opens the safety checks dialog for the macro in the pressed number slot"
msgstr ""
"Ouvre le dialogue des vérifications de sécurité pour la macro de "
"l'emplacement du chiffre pressé"

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that switches
#. to the previous macro stack.
msgid "Switches to the previous macro stack"
msgstr "Passe à la pile de macros précédente"

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that switches
#. to the next macro stack.
msgid "Switches to the next macro stack"
msgstr "Passe à la pile de macros suivante"

#. Translators: Announced when switching to a macro stack with no recorded macros.
#. {number} is the stack number.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Stack {number}, empty"
msgstr "Pile {number}, vide"

#. Translators: Announced when switching macro stacks.
#. {number} is the stack number and {count} how many macros it holds.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Stack {number}, {count} macro"
msgid_plural "Stack {number}, {count} macros"
msgstr[0] "Pile {number}, {count} macro"
msgstr[1] "Pile {number}, {count} macros"

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that lists the layer commands.
msgid "Speaks the commands available in the macros layer"
msgstr "Annonce les commandes disponibles dans la couche de macros"

#. Translators: Help message spoken when pressing h or f1 inside the macros layer.
msgid ""
"1 to 0: play the macro in that slot. Shift plus a number: record into that "
"slot. Alt plus a number: review speech and edit safety checks. Left and "
"right arrows: switch macro stacks. H or F1: this help. Escape: exit the "
"layer."
msgstr ""
"1 à 0 : lit la macro de cet emplacement. Maj plus un chiffre : enregistre "
"dans cet emplacement. Alt plus un chiffre : consulte la parole et modifie "
"les vérifications de sécurité. Flèches gauche et droite : change de pile de "
"macros. H ou F1 : cette aide. Échap : quitte la couche."

#. Translators: Input help description for the layer command that leaves the macros layer.
msgid "Exits the macros layer"
msgstr "Quitte la couche de macros"

#. Translators: Error announced when trying to record while a macro is playing.
msgid "Cannot record while a macro is playing"
msgstr "Impossible d'enregistrer pendant la lecture d'une macro"

#. Translators: Announced when macro recording starts.
#. {number} is the macro slot number.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Recording macro {number}"
msgstr "Enregistrement de la macro {number}"

#. Translators: Announced when recording ends without any keystrokes.
#. {number} is the macro slot number.
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Recording stopped. Macro {number} is unchanged because no keystrokes were "
"recorded"
msgstr ""
"Enregistrement arrêté. La macro {number} est inchangée car aucune frappe "
"n'a été enregistrée"

#. Translators: Announced when a macro has been recorded.
#. {number} is the macro slot number and {count} the amount of recorded keystrokes.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Macro {number} recorded with {count} keystroke"
msgid_plural "Macro {number} recorded with {count} keystrokes"
msgstr[0] "Macro {number} enregistrée avec {count} frappe"
msgstr[1] "Macro {number} enregistrée avec {count} frappes"

#. Translators: Error announced when the macros file cannot be written to disk.
msgid "Error saving macros"
msgstr "Erreur lors de la sauvegarde des macros"

#. Translators: Error announced when trying to start a macro while another is playing.
msgid "A macro is already playing"
msgstr "Une macro est déjà en cours de lecture"

#. Translators: Announced when the chosen macro slot has no recording.
#. {number} is the macro slot number.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Macro {number} is empty"
msgstr "La macro {number} est vide"

#. Translators: Error announced when a recorded keystroke cannot be replayed.
#. {key} is the name of the keystroke.
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Macro stopped: cannot send {key}"
msgstr "Macro arrêtée : impossible d'envoyer {key}"

#. Translators: Placeholder used in the safety check failure message
#. when NVDA spoke nothing at all after a keystroke.
msgid "nothing"
msgstr "rien"

#. Translators: Error announced when a macro safety check fails during playback.
#. {number} is the macro slot number, {step} the failing step number,
#. {key} the keystroke, {expected} the expected speech pattern
#. and {heard} what NVDA actually spoke.
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Macro {number} stopped at step {step}, {key}: expected speech matching "
"{expected} but heard {heard}"
msgstr ""
"Macro {number} arrêtée à l'étape {step}, {key} : parole attendue "
"correspondant à {expected} mais {heard} a été entendu"

#. Add-on description
#. Translators: Long description to be shown for this add-on on add-on information from add-on store
msgid ""
"Record and replay keyboard macros in ten stacks of ten slots.\n"
"Press NVDA+alt+shift+m to enter the macros layer, then press shift plus a "
"number to record,\n"
"a number to play, alt plus a number to edit the per-step speech safety "
"checks,\n"
"or the left and right arrows to switch stacks.\n"
"Recordings keep the pauses between keystrokes and everything NVDA spoke,\n"
"and playback can be stopped as soon as NVDA's speech no longer matches what "
"an enforced step expects."
msgstr ""
"Enregistre et lit des macros clavier dans dix piles de dix emplacements.\n"
"Appuyez sur NVDA+alt+shift+m pour entrer dans la couche de macros, puis "
"appuyez sur shift plus un chiffre pour enregistrer,\n"
"un chiffre pour lire, alt plus un chiffre pour modifier les vérifications "
"de sécurité de la parole par étape,\n"
"ou les flèches gauche et droite pour changer de pile.\n"
"Les enregistrements conservent les pauses entre les frappes et tout ce que "
"NVDA a prononcé,\n"
"et la lecture peut être arrêtée dès que la parole de NVDA ne correspond "
"plus à ce qu'attend une étape imposée."

#. Brief changelog for this version
#. Translators: what's new content for the add-on version to be shown in the add-on store
msgid ""
"Initial release: record and play keyboard macros with timing,\n"
"recorded speech, macro stacks, and optional per-step wildcard speech safety "
"checks."
msgstr ""
"Version initiale : enregistrement et lecture de macros clavier avec "
"temporisation,\n"
"parole enregistrée, piles de macros et vérifications de sécurité de la "
"parole optionnelles par étape avec jokers."
